<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span12"></div>
    <div class="span12">
        <div class="span6">
            <!-- Button to trigger modal -->
            <div class="span3">
                <a href="#about" role="button" class="btn btn-info span8 offset3" data-toggle="modal">About</a>

                <!-- Modal -->
                <div id="about" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="aboutLabel"
                     aria-hidden="true">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h3 id="aboutLabel">About</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <p>
                        <h5>Idea:</h5>
                        As a project for a school course, three students wanted to create a practical tool used to
                        generate outfits for people with a lot of choices and not enough time, given the pieces of
                        clothing available.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        <h5> Objective:</h5>
                        Shorten the time spent selecting clothes and matching them into appropriate attires.
                        Pick you own items or use a generated one and consider the weather when choosing one of
                        the suggested options.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="span3">
                <!-- Button to trigger modal -->
                <a href="#help" role="button" class="btn btn-info span8 offset3" data-toggle="modal">Help</a>

                <!-- Modal -->
                <div id="help" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="helpLabel"
                     aria-hidden="true">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h3 id="helpLabel">Help</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <h4>Instructions:</h4>

                        <p><h5>Creating an account:</h5> enter a username, password and e-mail as well as your birth
                        date
                        and
                        press <b>Register</b> in order to generate a new account.</p>

                        <p><h5>Logging in:</h5> If you already have an account, enter the e-mail and password used at
                        registration in the corresponding fields and press <b>Login</b>.</p>

                        <p><h5>Adding wardrobes:</h5> immediately after registering, press the <b>Add wardrobe</b>
                        button to create your first wardrobe. If you already have one created, press the
                        same button in the center of the page. After this, insert the name, location and
                        description of the newly created wardrobe and press <b>Create wardrobe</b>.</p>

                        <p><h5>Homepage:</h5> While you are on a page, clicking the <b>woRg</b> button in the top-left
                        corner will redirect you to the main page.</p>

                        <p><h5>Generating outfits:</h5> Start by clicking the <b>Dress me up!</b> button in
                        the top menu. Then select the search criteria you want and click <b>Show
                        me what I've got!</b> to see the results. There are two possible
                        outcomes: either the search returned no result, in which case
                        you can retry by clicking <b>Search again!</b>, or an
                        affirmative answer is shown telling you how many outfits
                        were generated. You can then check them out by pressing the
                        corresponding button.</p>

                        <p><h5>Selecting outfits:</h5> Each piece of clothing can be
                        individually selected from the suggested set. Proceed by
                        pressing <b>Take me to the dressing room</b> to see the
                        final outfit which you can either accept (and press <b>Yep!
                        I'll wear these!</b>) or reject and going back to
                        the results page (by selecting <b>No way! I am going
                        back to the results!</b>).</p>

                        <p><h5>Browsing wardrobes:</h5> The process of generating
                        and choosing an outfit can be done using the
                        clothes in each wardrobe. Simply select the
                        desired one from the drop-list <b>Wardrobes</b>
                        top menu and browse the items. You can also
                        add a piece of clothing by pressing the
                        corresponding button on the top-right,
                        entering the required parameters and
                        clicking <b>Save changes</b>.</p>

                        <p><h5>Changing the password:</h5> It can be done
                        from <b>Settings</b> in the top
                        menu.</p>

                        <p><h5>Preferences:</h5> Changeable by entering
                        the <b>Setting</b> page in the top
                        menu and selecting the first,
                        second and third favourite
                        color, material and model.</p>

                        <p><h5>Searching clothes:</h5> Entering a
                        keyword in the top-right corner
                        field will search all pieces of
                        clothing related to that query
                        (e.g. searching "stripes" will
                        generate a list of the clothes
                        in all wardrobes with a stripes
                        model).</p>

                        <p>In order to access this guide
                            again, press <b>Help</b> button
                            on the bottom of any page on
                            the website.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

